{"id":45247,"date":"2020-11-07T07:00:58","date_gmt":"2020-11-07T06:00:58","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/?p=45247"},"modified":"2022-01-18T15:32:38","modified_gmt":"2022-01-18T14:32:38","slug":"zalipie-painted-village-poland","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/poland\/zalipie-painted-village-poland\/","title":{"rendered":"Zalipie: The Beautiful Painted Village in Poland"},"content":{"rendered":"<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h2 id=\"h-the-story-of-zalipie-painted-village\">The Story of Zalipie Painted Village<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Over a hundred years ago in Zalipie, every house had a wood stove but no chimney. Thus, the smoke would create black marks on both the exterior and interior of the homes. To cover up the marks, the village women would go around painting flowers over the black soot. <\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"block-link block-link--readmore \">\n                <div class=\"block-link__container\">\n\n                    <div class=\"salt-icon__container\">\n                        <span class=\"salt-icon salt-icon--readmore\"><\/span>\n                        <svg class=\"icon icon-round-shape\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-round-shape\"><\/use><\/svg>\n                    <\/div>\n\n                    <p><strong>Discover more in our:<\/strong>&#xA0;<a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/poland\/poland-travel-guide\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">2-week travel guide through Poland<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n                <\/div>\n            <\/div>\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-2 is-cropped\"><ul class=\"blocks-gallery-grid\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/10\/23105951\/poland-zalipie-painted-village-540x810.jpg\" alt=\"poland zalipie painted village\"><\/noscript><img width=\"226\" height